{
  "text": "Applying a 1 mW kg \u03ea1 heating perturbation only over 150-80 mb is more realistic since longwave radiation is the only parameterization that can vary significantly in that domain. The response (\u03f34 K) is comparable to the responses seen in Fig. 2 for the parameterization changes. The response decreases rapidly below the forcing region. [CITATION_1] showed that very thin cirrus clouds observed near the tropopause have longwave heating rates of \u03f310 mW kg",
